**

31:55.447 --> 32:00.419
* This ancient life

32:00.452 --> 32:02.488
**

32:02.521 --> 32:03.389
* This ancient life

32:03.422 --> 32:06.058
Knife.

32:06.092 --> 32:07.026
* Mm-mm-mm

32:10.096 --> 32:21.140
**

32:21.173 --> 32:23.042
3 hours, 30 minutes.

32:23.075 --> 32:25.177
You didn't want him on bypass
any longer than five hours.

32:25.211 --> 32:30.116
**

32:30.149 --> 32:33.519
"Wynken and Blynken
are two little eyes,

32:33.552 --> 32:37.189
and Nod is a little head,

32:37.223 --> 32:39.658
and the wooden shoe
that sailed the skies

32:39.691 --> 32:41.994
is a wee one's trundle-bed.

32:42.028 --> 32:48.134
[ Voice breaking ] So shut your
eyes while Mother sings --

32:48.167 --> 32:51.170
**

32:51.203 --> 32:52.538
Melendez:
How's it look, Dr. Murphy?

32:52.571 --> 32:55.741
**

32:55.774 --> 32:58.244
14 millimeters.

32:58.277 --> 33:00.212
Exactly.

33:00.246 --> 33:01.247
Perfect.

33:01.280 --> 33:04.383
**

33:04.416 --> 33:06.518
His septal tissue...

33:06.552 --> 33:11.157
**

33:11.190 --> 33:13.792
It's stiffer
than I anticipated.

33:13.825 --> 33:22.201
**

33:22.234 --> 33:24.603
I don't think this is gonna be
enough for adequate outflow.

33:24.636 --> 33:29.141
**

33:29.175 --> 33:32.178
I'm taking the septum
down to 13.

33:32.211 --> 33:36.115
Okay, the valve
wasn't supported at 13.

33:36.148 --> 33:37.383
The patient died.

33:37.416 --> 33:39.118
That was a model,
not a patient.

33:39.151 --> 33:42.721
We're at five hours
and three minutes.

33:42.754 --> 33:47.726
**

33:47.759 --> 33:49.661
We're taking him down
to 13.

33:49.695 --> 33:56.302
**

33:56.335 --> 33:59.071
Field.

33:59.105 --> 34:02.174
All quiet
for the time-out.

34:02.208 --> 34:03.675
Patient is
Elizabeth McLaren.

34:03.709 --> 34:04.810
No known allergies.

34:04.843 --> 34:07.179
We'll be doing
a total laryngectomy

34:07.213 --> 34:08.714
with a Gluck Sorenson
U-shaped incision.

34:08.747 --> 34:09.681
Is everyone in agreement?

34:11.483 --> 34:12.718
Antibiotics in?

34:12.751 --> 34:14.586
One gram of cefotaxime
has been infused.

34:14.620 --> 34:15.854
We anticipate a specimen.

34:15.887 --> 34:17.789
I've requested
labels be printed.

34:17.823 --> 34:20.126
Pen.

34:20.159 --> 34:21.727
Prepare to intubate.

34:23.562 --> 34:24.696
Dentures.

34:25.864 --> 34:27.699
You've gotta hold
the surgery.

34:27.733 --> 34:30.402
Uh...just give me
a little time.

34:30.436 --> 34:35.307
**

34:35.341 --> 34:37.509
That's 13.

34:37.543 --> 34:43.582
**

34:43.615 --> 34:45.851
Dammit.
[ Breathes deeply ]

34:45.884 --> 34:48.387
Too thin?

34:48.420 --> 34:52.691
The valve doesn't have
adequate support.

34:52.724 --> 34:54.526
It won't be able to close.

34:54.560 --> 34:57.763
**

34:57.796 --> 34:59.498
I was wrong.

34:59.531 --> 35:09.575
**

35:09.608 --> 35:13.645
**

35:13.679 --> 35:14.846
Whoa.

35:14.880 --> 35:17.849
There's
a reattachment point.

35:17.883 --> 35:19.751
We must not have seen it
at 14

35:19.785 --> 35:22.354
'cause it was obscured
by the subvalvular tissue.

35:22.388 --> 35:25.891
We can use that as an anchor
point and move the valve.

35:25.924 --> 35:28.427
Your terrible idea just got
a hell of a lot better.

35:28.460 --> 35:29.495
Stitch.

35:29.528 --> 35:32.231
5 hours, 23 minutes.

35:32.264 --> 35:42.241
**

35:42.274 --> 35:47.246
**

35:47.279 --> 35:48.347
Hey.

35:48.380 --> 35:49.615
Dentures.

35:49.648 --> 35:50.716
They always end up
in the wrong cup,

35:50.749 --> 35:52.684
which is why they're so hard
to get back to the owner.

35:52.718 --> 35:54.286
Okay.
Right.

35:54.320 --> 35:55.854
What if the label
on the specimen was wrong?

35:55.887 --> 35:58.257
What -- What if the nodule
is here,

35:58.290 --> 35:59.825
but the container
has the wrong name on it?

35:59.858 --> 36:01.693
Okay, I'm reconciling
the operative records

36:01.727 --> 36:03.662
to the surgery schedule
to the specimen.

36:03.695 --> 36:05.664
I'll read the cases,
check the containers,

36:05.697 --> 36:06.932
and feel like a jerk
for judging you.

36:06.965 --> 36:09.335
Well, you're only a jerk
if I'm right.

36:09.368 --> 36:11.937
**

36:11.970 --> 36:13.872
Pump time?

36:13.905 --> 36:16.208
6 hours, 48 minutes.

36:16.242 --> 36:20.779
**

36:20.812 --> 36:22.748
Get Mehta in here.

36:23.949 --> 36:26.218
Let's take him off bypass.

36:31.257 --> 36:41.233
**

36:41.267 --> 36:51.243
**

36:51.277 --> 36:55.681
**

36:55.714 --> 36:56.782
12 seconds.

36:56.815 --> 36:57.949
Should I get the paddles?

36:57.983 --> 36:59.551
Not yet.

36:59.585 --> 37:00.552
Come on, Gabriel.

37:01.953 --> 37:03.822
How long
has he been on bypass?

37:03.855 --> 37:05.357
Nearly two hours too long.
We need to jump-start --

37:05.391 --> 37:06.725
Not yet!

37:06.758 --> 37:09.661
**

37:09.695 --> 37:13.865
[ Monitor beeping slowly ]

37:15.367 --> 37:16.368
Yeah.

37:16.402 --> 37:18.470
Yes!

37:18.504 --> 37:20.472
[ Sighs ]

37:20.506 --> 37:24.042
**

37:24.075 --> 37:26.545
Dr. Murphy, close him up.

37:26.578 --> 37:28.547
[ Allman Brown's
"Sons and Daughters" plays ]

37:28.580 --> 37:34.586
* And I will hold you tight
[ Pounding ]

37:34.620 --> 37:39.558
* Like the moon
in the arms of the sky *

37:39.591 --> 37:40.992
[ Pounding continues ]

37:41.026 --> 37:47.399
* And I will keep you warm

37:47.433 --> 37:48.667
* I will build a fire
in this house *

37:48.700 --> 37:53.605
It's beating just fine
on its own.

37:53.639 --> 37:55.407
* And I'll build a fire

37:55.441 --> 38:00.479
* You fetch the water,
and I'll lay the table *

38:00.512 --> 38:05.584
* And in our hearts, we still
pray for sons and daughters *

38:05.617 --> 38:07.519
Marcus.

38:07.553 --> 38:09.921
* And all those evenings
out in the garden *

38:09.955 --> 38:12.658
* The red, red wine

38:12.691 --> 38:16.795
* These quiet hours
turning to years *

38:16.828 --> 38:18.664
[ Breathing shakily ]

38:18.697 --> 38:22.868
There was a specimen cup in
the O.R. prior to your surgery.

38:22.901 --> 38:25.371
It was supposed to be used
for a bullet removal,

38:25.404 --> 38:27.906
but they left the bullet
in the body,

38:27.939 --> 38:31.343
and the cup was used
accidentally for your specimen.

38:31.377 --> 38:34.045
Not only was it
in formalin,

38:34.079 --> 38:37.349
but it was refrigerated
and fresh as a daisy.

38:37.383 --> 38:40.619
Elizabeth,
you don't have cancer.

38:40.652 --> 38:43.489
[ Crying ]

38:46.692 --> 38:49.595
Thank you.

38:49.628 --> 38:51.863
Doctor.

38:53.932 --> 38:55.567
* And I'll build a fire

38:55.601 --> 39:00.506
* You fetch the water,
and I'll lay the table *

39:00.539 --> 39:04.510
* And in our hearts, we still
pray for sons and daughters *

39:04.543 --> 39:06.745
[ Laughs ]

39:06.778 --> 39:08.780
* And all those evenings
out in the garden *

39:08.814 --> 39:10.449
Intangibles.

39:10.482 --> 39:13.619
* The red, red wine

39:13.652 --> 39:20.392
* These quiet hours
turning to years *

39:20.426 --> 39:21.593
Hello.

39:21.627 --> 39:22.994
Hello.

39:23.028 --> 39:24.162
I had
a very good day today.

39:24.195 --> 39:24.963
Yes, you did.

39:24.996 --> 39:26.498
That was
a hell of an operation.

39:26.532 --> 39:27.699
Yes.

39:27.733 --> 39:29.535
And I caught
Claire flirting.

39:29.568 --> 39:30.602
With you?

39:30.636 --> 39:31.670
Shaun, I think
you might be mis--

39:31.703 --> 39:33.672
With Dr. Melendez.

39:33.705 --> 39:34.673
Ah, Dr. Melendez.

39:34.706 --> 39:36.475
I conducted observations,

39:36.508 --> 39:38.544
successfully interpreted them,
and logged them.

39:38.577 --> 39:40.579
Romance in a spreadsheet.

39:40.612 --> 39:42.113
I love it.

39:42.147 --> 39:46.418
I was aware of the cues
even when Claire wasn't.

39:46.452 --> 39:48.787
I think
she needs a life-skills coach.

39:48.820 --> 39:49.921
Extrapolating.

39:49.955 --> 39:50.956
I like that, too.

39:50.989 --> 39:52.458
That's great, Shaun.

39:52.491 --> 39:54.460
You're paying attention.
You're learning.

39:54.493 --> 39:57.028
And when we find you
a life coach,

39:57.062 --> 39:58.564
one with a fashion sense,

39:58.597 --> 40:00.065
then you're gonna be
learning better,

40:00.098 --> 40:02.033
you're gonna be
learning faster.

40:02.067 --> 40:04.836
**

40:04.870 --> 40:07.473
Are you giving up on me?

40:07.506 --> 40:10.008
What?

40:10.041 --> 40:12.444
No.
I haven't given up on you.

40:12.478 --> 40:15.113
I don't want
a stranger helping me.

40:15.146 --> 40:17.516
I know, Shaun.

40:17.549 --> 40:19.751
But...

40:19.785 --> 40:22.854
And I can't [Sighs]

40:22.888 --> 40:24.222
I can't always be there.

40:24.255 --> 40:25.390
I-I..

40:25.423 --> 40:29.094
I can't always help you
the way you need to be helped,

40:29.127 --> 40:31.029
the way
you deserve to be helped.

40:31.062 --> 40:33.532
I don't want
a stranger helping me.

40:33.565 --> 40:36.902
**

40:36.935 --> 40:40.038
[ Door opens ]

40:40.071 --> 40:42.474
[ Door closes ]

40:42.508 --> 40:46.077
**

40:46.111 --> 40:47.613
Claire:
Congratulations.

40:47.646 --> 40:49.715
You too.

40:49.748 --> 40:51.783
On your mad
sleuthing skills.

40:51.817 --> 40:54.085
Something to fall back on
if this surgery thing gets old.

40:54.119 --> 40:56.221
[ Laughs ]

40:56.254 --> 40:58.189
Jessica:
You did a nice job, Claire.

40:58.223 --> 41:00.792
Thanks.
And here is our price tag.

41:00.826 --> 41:02.060
We've been served.

41:02.093 --> 41:04.630
But we found it.
Elizabeth's fine.

41:04.663 --> 41:05.897
I know.

41:05.931 --> 41:07.833
But we put her
through two days of hell,

41:07.866 --> 41:09.735
and she wants to make sure it
doesn't happen to anybody else.

41:09.768 --> 41:10.769
I mean, good for her.

41:13.772 --> 41:16.508
What is this?

41:16.542 --> 41:18.243
Gabriel's pacemaker.

41:18.276 --> 41:20.579
I heard you were
brilliant again today.

41:22.548 --> 41:23.615
I got lucky.

41:23.649 --> 41:28.920
**

41:28.954 --> 41:31.757
Do you think Armen would kill
me if I got a pet hedgehog?

41:31.790 --> 41:33.124
I mean, I read that
they're actually pretty --

41:33.158 --> 41:35.126
Lea.
Yes, Shaun?

41:36.161 --> 41:38.664
You look absurd
in that sweater.

41:38.697 --> 41:44.936
**

41:44.970 --> 41:47.906
I have apples.

41:47.939 --> 41:50.208
Do you want an apple?

41:52.277 --> 41:54.780
Yeah.

41:54.813 --> 41:57.148
[ Lock disengages, door opens ]

